{"title": "Mexico and the United States: a Story of Revolution, Intervention and War", "description": "Starr, being an anthropologist and a historian, visited Mexico extensively. As he wrote this book, a highly disruptive, deadly revolution was taking place across the nation, so Starr attempts to explain the circumstances leading to that event.  He begins with the Centennial of Independence, then delves into the country's history starting with the Aztecs, and up to present day (1914). The point of view from both countries protagonists is also discussed as historic events are described. He states that \"the US and Mexico are different, yet they are neighbors.\", and ends with \"They should be friends.\" - Summary by Mario Pineda", "duration": 43715, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18166", "name": "Frederick Starr"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/mexicousrevolutionandwar_2406_librivox/mexicounitedstates_2406.jpg", "copyright_year": "1914", "genres": ["Early Modern", "Modern (19th C)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mario Pineda"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Christine Rottger"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "KHand"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Preface", "readers": [3796], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mexicousrevolutionandwar_2406_librivox/mxusstory_01_starr_64kb.mp3", "duration": 313}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Centennial", "readers": [11281], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mexicousrevolutionandwar_2406_librivox/mxusstory_02_starr_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1493}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Centennial, continued", "readers": [11281], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mexicousrevolutionandwar_2406_librivox/mxusstory_03_starr_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1891}, {"section": 4, "title": "Aquiles Serd\u00e1n", "readers": [11281], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/mexicousrevolutionandwar_2406_librivox/mxusstory_04